http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Officials-suspended-for-non-delivery-of-Paswan%E2%80%99s-New-Year-greeting-cards/article13997839.ece

Three officials of the Department of Posts in Bihar were suspended on Wednesday for non-delivery of the New Year greeting cards from Lok Jan Shakti Party chief and Union Minister Ram Vilas Paswan to the people of Hajipur, which he represents in the Lok Sabha.Party leaders brought the issue to the notice of Mr. Paswan when he visited Hajipur in Vaishali district recently.“After receiving a compliant that the cards were dumped in a building, I ordered an inquiry. The complaint was found to be true, and preliminary action was taken against three officials,” District Postal Superintendent Umesh Chand Prasad said.Those who have been suspended are Lallan Ram, postmaster of the Hajipur main post office, Raj Kumar Shrivastva, PRO, and postman Deonarayan Mahto.More than 450 greeting cards sent by Mr. Paswan were found strewn on the third floor of the District Bar Council building.“Many party workers and people of the district complained that they had not received the greeting cards from Mr. Paswan,” district LJP president Awadhesh Kumar Singh said. When the cards were found strewn in the bar council office, we moved the Postal Superintendent.The Department of Posts arranged to distribute the cards “as soon as possible,” Mr. Prasad said.